  "summary": "Moderate: ruby:3.1 security, bug fix, and enhancement update",
  "details": "Ruby is an extensible, interpreted, object-oriented, scripting language. It has features to process text files and to perform system management tasks.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* ruby: RCE vulnerability with .rdoc_options in RDoc (CVE-2024-27281)\n* ruby: Buffer overread vulnerability in StringIO (CVE-2024-27280)\n* ruby: Arbitrary memory address read vulnerability with Regex search (CVE-2024-27282)\n\nFor detailed information on changes in this release, see the AlmaLinux Release Notes linked from the References section.",
